headline: The AI Bubble May Have Already Popped. The Rally Can Still Survive.
summary: FEATURE  It wasn’t too long ago that the mere mention of “artificial intelligence” in a corporate press release would trigger an upside move for the stock.  Investors, eager to get ahead of the next wave of the new technology’s potential, were happy to believe in, and bet on, a bottom-line impact from AI deployment—even if it couldn’t be fully explained.

headline: Alphabet Gets Close to Passing Microsoft in Market Cap
summary: If Alphabet keeps climbing, it might soon surpass Microsoft in total market cap for the first time in seven years.  Alphabet stock got a boost late last week after a filing showed that Warren Buffett’s Berkshire Hathaway purchased 17.8 million shares of the company during the third quarter.  On Tuesday, Alphabet launched Gemini 3, an updated version of its own large language model — offering a chance to gain some ground in the artificial intelligence arms race.

headline: Alphabet Shares Soar on ‘Rave Reviews’ for New Gemini AI Model
summary: More than 376,000 call options on Alphabet changed hands as of 11:00 a.m. in New York, above the 20-day average of about 290,000 for a full day of trading.  The Google parent on Tuesday launched the latest version of its Gemini artificial intelligence model, which was met with glowing reviews about its capabilities.  “In addition to benefits to Search engagement and monetization, Google also combines real-time web indexing with advanced model training, which we view as a key competitive advantage,” he wrote.

headline: South Korea Antitrust Regulators Inspect Arm’s Office in Seoul
summary: The Korea Fair Trade Commission is conducting the unannounced inspections of Arm as part of an inquiry into its conduct, said the people, who were granted anonymity to discuss a confidential matter.  The move stems in part from a complaint by Qualcomm Inc. alleging that Arm is hurting competition by restricting access to its technology after operating an open network for more than 20 years, the people said.  Spokespeople for Arm and Qualcomm declined to comment.

headline: Asian markets bounce as Nvidia takes centre stage amid AI bubble fears
summary: Asian investors battled Wednesday to kickstart a recovery in equities following the latest stagger across world markets that has been caused by worries over an AI-fuelled bubble and uncertainty over US interest rates.Also in sight this week is the planned release of key US data, particularly on jobs creation, which will be closely read over for an idea about the Fed's plans for interest rates.
